##
# raid - 
# $Header: /opt/cvsroot/doc/tech/raid,v 1.2 2006/08/10 17:11:27 jick Exp $

= Document =
 * http://www.tldp.org/HOWTO/Software-RAID-HOWTO.html

= RAID levels =
 * Linear mode (JBOD)
 * RAID-0 (strip mode)
 * RAID-1 (mirror)
 * RAID-4 (not used very often)
 * RAID-5 (perhaps most useful RAID mode)
 * Nested RAID: 0+1, 10, 50

= mdadm =
 * Linear: 
 * mdadm --create --verbose /dev/md0 --level=linear --raid-devices=2 /dev/sdb6 /dev/sdc5

